##The real picture of people buying vegetables in Wuhan

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

They understand the closure of the community, understand can only choose to be stuffed with four bags of dumplings group purchase package, understand the food prices doubled, understand to continue to endure the inconvenience of life, it is possible to wait a little earlier to end the day.

| Chan Xie, editor | Roo

Wuhan Yazi Wang Jiaxing called his parents and learned that the 100 yuan vegetable package recommended by the community owners was only 70 yuan on weekdays. When he hung up, it was up almost 50% . "Wuhan sister-in-law Han scolds" after the video became popular, he looked up on his mobile phone the price of vegetables announced by a supermarket in Wuhan: 8.5 yuan / Jin for tomatoes, and 4050 yuan / Jin for meat..

"I can only comfort myself that we are finally free from the daily life-and-death tweets and can start to focus on eating, " the young man wrote on his social media account

For the millions trapped in Wuhan, almost everyone understands the peculiarities of a particular time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
And setting the alarm won't get us a delivery slot

Cheng Wei set the alarm clock every day, but never grabbed the box Ma Xiansheng distribution quota. He says the list is disappearing as fast as a Tetris. Hakuh Sh compares the distribution of Ma Xiansheng robbed box to: And SNKRS Nike official APP rob a pair of AJ, every day running with.

After the closure of the city, traffic control and block policy followed. Online shopping has become a major channel.

On February 11, Su Zhang's Mother's community group began to be popular WECHAT group Longtuan purchase. They added a bunch of wechat groups, some by brand, some by type of shopping. Residential Property told them that now the size of the group there are 30, almost all by their own businesses.

Residential property has to Su Zhang mother recommended a small procedure to buy food. Small procedures to buy meat 1000 yuan to send, but Su Zhangs did not dare to go home before the outbreak, the home of two people, simply can not eat so much meat.

Su Zhang studied a bit before he figured out how to order vegetables online. She placed orders remotely, and her parents armed themselves to the teeth to pick up the food at the designated spot. She sometimes thought: "If only the elderly family, really do not know how to buy food. "

Young people who help their parents shop online:

Add 100 yuan to get a red envelope

Liu Yi bought a meal for his parents on the 17th through hungry. That is a friend taught her method, a friend told, to give the rider 200 yuan red envelope, someone will pick up the order.

Their community only two buildings, few families in, before the intervention of the community staff, the owners themselves can not gather enough group purchase to send the need to achieve the number of orders.

Liu Yi's parents had been in Japan with her for the Lunar New Year, and their visas could not be renewed, so they returned to Wuhan on Feb. 17 by a chartered plane from the embassy. Come back that day the old man went out to buy food, just to the gate of the community was stopped. Liu Yi also flustered, on micro-blog a look, just know Wuhan all residential areas have been closed management.

They have come at a time of the strictest controls: the previous policy of allowing one person per household to go out every three days to buy food has lapsed, and passes have been revoked.

But Liu Yi thinks he's lucky. She only paid 100 yuan for the dispatch fee and had a rider to take the order. She chose some longer storage time dishes, according to four or five catties for units to buy, hope to buy food can support a few more days.

"It's not completely out of reach, it's just too expensive, " she said, clearly sensing that the order was more expensive than usual, costing nearly 500 yuan, not counting the running expenses. "Special Times, no way. "

Liu Yi's order for 500 yuan.

Shang Chao no longer docking individuals, can only buy packages

Since February 18, Wuchang District and castle peak districts have announced that all merchants in their districts will only accept group purchase customers and will no longer sell daily necessities to individuals.

A number of supermarkets launched a group purchase package. Su Zhang residential area commonly used Carrefour Guanggu shop set meal, the general family demand is larger vegetables and meat. There are 11 kinds of vegetables in the vegetable set meal, the price is 99 yuan. The frozen meat set meal consists of 2.5 kg of hind leg meat, 2.5 kg of rib meat and 2 kg of streaky pork. The price is 349 yuan.

WECHAT group to buy vegetables, residents complain about 100 yuan to buy the vegetable package, usually only 30 yuan. The number of Tangyuan bags in one package increased daily -- from two to four -- "it wasn't like a big family celebrating the Lantern Festival

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Government Wechat public accounts have been recommended to the residents of the online platform for fresh. As of February 24, the number of e-commerce platforms offering online shopping services in Wuhan had increased to 33, according to Wuhan, an E-commerce company that has attracted business. Each platform has different requirements for delivery time, delivery time limit and delivery scope. Most platforms have requirements on the number of group purchases, or the need for a fixed "head" docking.

Qin Chuke, who lives in Wuhan, recorded his experiences buying food through these online channels on his wechat account. He tried at least nine of the APPS, and there are many reasons why he couldn't buy food:

There is no contact person in the community on the APP, so you can not buy it. The multi-point APP page of Zhongbai Warehouse Shows "convenient life, please look forward to" . The MEIJIA has made three unsuccessful appointments...

On the evening of the 22nd, a video of a "Wuhan sister-in-law scolding" suddenly became an Internet hit: an owner in a community group attacked the inactive community and the supermarket, which was sold as a package deal. Chen Weijia saw the video, can not help but think, these live in Wuhan high-end residential owners can only be at the mercy of the package, then others?

Wu Shang Supermarket (February 17-february 20 package prices) is divided into two sets of vegetables, six vegetable combinations (7.5kg 58 yuan / portion) and eight vegetable combinations (9.5kg 88 yuan / portion). The meat and eggs package includes 5 catties of frozen pork, 30 eggs and a carton of plain milk for 162 yuan. Zhongbai Warehouse Only Shows One Vegetable Combo as an example, containing seven vegetables and one portion of scallion, ginger, and garlic, for 80 yuan.

"Wuhan has a lot of villages in the city, or old neighborhoods that are about to be torn down and half-demolished. Each one has only one or two security guards. Can they manage it? "

Chen Weijia felt that being in an epidemic area, seeing the number of confirmed cases rise every day, people in Wuhan at this stage, "really depressed and have a strong sense of crisis, and then a high-priced group purchase, don't say much grievance in my heart. "

Previously, Chen Weijia feel home in Wuhan's mother is still good, a monthly pension, but not necessarily around the neighbors. "Some elderly people in Wuhan are very frugal. My neighbors buy a dollar bag of instant noodles every time they go to the supermarket. " One neighbor complained to Sun Wei's mother every day that he could not go out to earn money. What if he ran out of money. Mother Chen can only comfort each other, now is a difficult time, we all endure.

"Wuhan sister-in-law Han scold" after the video fire, Wu merchants and warehouse in the 24th and 25th have updated the package. Compared with the two-tier packages, all kinds of package prices have been reduced, and the price of a single item is also identified.

According to a report in Hubei daily on the 25th, five major commercial supermarkets in Wuhan have all launched 10 catties and 10 yuan special vegetable bags, saying that they will focus on guaranteeing the purchase of low-income groups in their jurisdiction. But there is no specific explanation of the "low-income Group" criterion.

Marginal communities that have lost their steady supply of vegetables

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Listen to Tao community residents to the city message board message.

Communicate with the community, call the mayor's hotline over and over, leave a message on the city message board... Wuhan Girl Zhang Yixiu and her friends tried every conceivable way to solve the problem of buying vegetables. There's no steady supply of food in their community.

Community residents jokingly call themselves "enclaves. ". Zhang Yixiu's community is located in the Wuhan Economic Development Zone. It is called Jingkai district Fengshu road for short. Its geographical location is Jingkai district. The surrounding communities are all under the management of Jingkai district. Only her Tingtao community belongs to Caidian District. In fact, they're 22 kilometers from downtown Caidian District.

Since the city was sealed off, Zhang Yixiu watched the doors of the market close one after another.

At the gate of the community, the Zhongbai supermarket was forced to close because the food license did not reach the store, where the entire community was thousands of residents shopping security.

The owner of the self-employed shop, no. 18, has also been told on wechat group that he will not be able to get food and fruit in the future because of further traffic control.

Zhang Yixiu tried one of the six online shopping platforms recommended online, five of which did not include their community distribution. There was only one APP, and residents started tours in remote locations, only to stop after a day or two.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Zhang Yixiu and friends try to solve the problem of the work diary

Many owners hope that they can have a regular business with the community interface. From time to time, there are private owners selling vegetables in the owners'group. Zhang Yixiu said that the problem of price increases depends entirely on the conscience of the sellers. Even some people often send news in the group that stores will be closed on the last few months to incite everyone to hurry up with reserve supplies.

During the ongoing negotiations, they arrived on the 21st with the only group purchase organized in the name of the community: a 55 yuan vegetable bag.

Community: 4 staff versus 2,500 households

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
February 24, in Wuhan Baibu Pavilion Community Longting Community, Baibu Pavilion Community Four Neighborhood Committee staff and volunteers for residents to organize their ordered goods. (Xinhua News Agency)

Zhang feels that the problems in the community are circular: She believes that what she tells the community, the community must have told her. She and her friends called the mayor's hotline again and again, but each time the response was to urge the street office or the community to fix it for them.

The pressure eventually returned to a community of four workers. According to the Community Secretary, more than 2,500 families, or 7,000 people, now live in Tingtao. Except for the sinking cadre who came to help, the community didn't even have grid workers. One of the grid workers did not return from the field to Wuhan, and the other had just given birth.

According to the Community Secretary, the office calls seem to go on 24 hours a day. She and her colleagues have been living in the community for more than a month and have not returned home, leaving work at 8 pm is the norm.

Every day when they go to work, the demands of the residents pour in on them. Any family that needed to buy the medicine would tell her how bad it would be if it wasn't there today. As for food, the residents have various demands: "He who buys vegetables wants meat; he who eats meat wants fresh meat, not frozen meat; he who eats fresh meat, says I want fish; he who eats fish, says I want wine, I want potato chips... "

A resident asked if she could change the vegetables in her bag. She was completely helpless. "This is the season to eat these dishes, isn't it? "

As for the lack of a large supermarket to link up with the community, the secretary explained that they had previously contacted the nearest Wushu supermarket in the district, but that when it came to cross-district issues, the other supermarket could not deliver goods and their own community could not go out without a pass. The problem lingered on.

Before the press release, Zhang Yixiu and friends said they had received complaints from the Caidian District market supervision bureau, who told them that starting from the 25th, the Zhongbai Listening to Tao Guanhai store at the gate of the residential area could continue to supply the community, in addition to the temporary lack of meat, basic rice, flour, oil, vegetables have.

On the same day, the community staff also announced a new group purchase method in the owner group, said that they have been in good communication with the hill shop, like other residents in the same normal group purchase. But the workload is so heavy that the community is hoping to recruit 16 volunteers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A screenshot of the community recruiting volunteers on Wechat

The problem of buying vegetables in the eyes of the sinking cadres

On January 27, Fu Shasha was stationed in the Baimazhou community as a sunken cadre. According to statistics on February 23, there are 2,098 families and 4,200 people in Baimazhou community. Ms. Fu said she had worked hard on buying food for her community.

At first, she contacted the familiar vegetable seller, let the other side to pull vegetables to sell at the gate of the community. But when the residents saw the food, they poured in. She decided it was too dangerous and started looking for online delivery stores.

She found a total of 13 shops, one by one to verify the business license, health certificates, quarantine certificates, and so on, she recommended to residents to buy.

She also contacted two supermarket owners in the community, let residents in the wechat group order, a good row, whose turn to go downstairs to get food.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fu Shasha delivers vegetables to the residents of the community

Shang Chao announced the news of the docking community out, Fu Shasha contacted the staff of Wu merchants. She was handed a form and opened it. It was full of packages, leaving her little choice. Even the spices come with a special set menu.

"Many residents are frugal and don't want to splurge. We young people don't mind buying soy sauce and buying this and that, but some older people don't want to buy those packages. "

That time, there was no successful docking with the vendors, Fu Shasha said, another reason is that the package needs the community to send their own car to pick up. But there are only two cars in the community, used to buy medicine for the residents, or to deal with other emergencies. The Community car also has a written regulation, can not be used for other purposes.

At present, Wuhan residents mainly rely on online fresh platform and community organizations to buy food channels. In addition, some community residents said that the home neighborhood convenience store can still be ordered through wechat group, but also some community owners rely on their own resources, contact familiar vegetable vendors to the community owners from time to time. "Don't look at the price when you buy food, just grab it! "
